  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     Neural Scaling Laws
Category:    Theory
Definition:  Performance improves predictably with compute/data/parameters
Year:        2020
Researchers: Kaplan et al.
Applications:LLM development, compute planning
Related:     Chinchilla scaling, emergent abilities

Concept:     RLHF
Category:    Training technique
Definition:  Fine-tunes LLMs using human preference comparisons
Year:        2017
Researchers: Christiano et al.
Applications:ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini alignment
Related:     PPO, reward model, preference learning

Concept:     Mixture of Experts
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Sparse model activating different expert subsets per token
Year:        2017
Researchers: Shazeer et al.
Applications:Large LLMs (Mixtral, rumored GPT-4)
Related:     Sparse activation, routing, scaling efficiency

